-- Pro Kapital Plans Housing, Retail Projects in Estonia, Latvia
-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 2012-03-13T10:12:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/pro-kapital-plans-housing-retail-projects-in-estonia-latvia.html
Pro Kapital Grupp (PRO) , an Estonian
property developer, said it plans “substantial” residential
developments and a shopping mall in Estonia and  Latvia  as the
Baltic real-estate market is improving.  The Tallinn-based company is adding three new members to
its board. They are Pertti Huuskonen, the chairman of
 Technopolis Plc (TPS1V) , Petri Olkinuora, the former chief executive
officer of  Citycon Oyj (CTY1S) , and Sari Aitokallio, the former finance
chief of Sponda Plc, Pro Kapital said in a  statement  on its
website today.  The company is 25 percent owned by Italian businessman
Ernesto Preatoni.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
